Autonomic Governance: Built-in integrity verification mechanisms that perform automated structural pruning to prevent logical drift.

Zero-Trust Footprint: Minimalist dependency footprint designed for high-availability environments where resource overhead must be near-zero.

Audit-Ready Design: All structural transitions are governed by strict state-machine protocols, ensuring full provenance of system changes.

